Quote: Not so [jovial] Mr Govett, the vicar, who is innocent & naive enough to fear the corruption that these worthies may introduce into his cure. This fear of spoiling their `happy valleys' has been epidemic on the ministry here, and has made the missionaries oppose colonization and led them to vamp up all the nauseous maudlin maori fancying stuff that has caused disaster ... here...
Notes: (J.C. Richmond)

