Date: 18/11/1877
Source: Letter
Author: T.S.GRACE
Vol / Page: 286
Edition: 1928
Quote: In early years they [Natives] received Christianity - and I may say Colonization- at our hands without doubting, and, to a great extent, on credit. Colonization, war, confiscation and English vices have followed each other in quick succession, while the expectations anticipated from representations made when they signed the `Treaty of Waitangi' have not been realized.
Notes: 1877 Nov 18 T.S.Grace letter in Grace Pioneer Missionary (1928) 286

